<h1 style="color:#00cccc;">Statistics</h1>
<p>11 teens die every day as a result of texting while driving</p>
<p>The National Safety Council reports that cell phone use while driving leads to 1.6 million crashes each year</p>
<p>Nearly 330,000 injuries occur each year from accidents caused by texting while driving</p>
<p>Texting while driving is 6x more likely to cause an accident than driving drunk</p>
<p>21% of teen drivers involved in fatal accidents were distracted by their cell phones</p>
<p>The Virginia Tech Transportation Institute found that text messaging creates a crash risk 23 times worse than driving while not distracted</p>
<p>1 out of every 4 car accidents in the United States is caused by texting and driving</p>
<p>Teens who text while driving spend approximately 10% of their driving time outside of their lane</p>
<p>In 2014, 3,179 people were killed, and 431,000 were injured in motor vehicle crashes involving distracted drivers </p>
